\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 9. A. sphaeromorpha} Iljin,{\i  Bull. Jard. Bot. URSS}{\b  26:} 414 (1927). Much-branched annual up to 80 cm. Leaves up to 3 × 2 cm, triangular-ovate or deltate, broadly cuneate, obtuse, crenate-serrate, grey-green. Female flowers few, axillary; male terminal, in short, leafless, spicate inflorescences. Bracteoles c. 6 mm, rhombic, irregularly dentate, ventricose, becoming hardened towards the base.{\i  S.E. Russia and S. Ukraine.} Rs(W, E).
\par

