\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 13. A. recurva} D'Urv., {\i Mém. Soc. Linn. Paris}{\b  1:} 284 (1822) ({\i A. tatarica} subsp. {\i recurva} (D'Urv.) Rech. fil.). Prostrate, shrubby perennial 10-40 cm. Leaves up to 7 × 5 cm, similar in shape to those of {\b 12}. Inflorescence terminal, leafless. Bracteoles up to 20 mm, rhombic to orbicular, without or with small dorsal appendages. 2n = 18. • {\i Coasts of S. & C. Aegean region.} Cr Gr.
