\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 15. A. patens} (Litv.) Iljin,{\i  Bull. Jard. Bot. URSS}{\b  26:} 415 (1927). Erect annual 15-70 cm. Lower and middle leaves up to 8 × 2 cm, narrowly oblong-hastate to elliptic-lanceolate, crenate-serrate, the upper linear-lanceolate, entire. Cymes small, in leafless, terminal, spicate inflorescences. Bracteoles orbicular-deltate, acuminate, entire or dentate, farinose, smooth or muricate dorsally.{\i  S. Russia Ukraine.} Rs(C, W, E).
