\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 16. A. patula} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 1053 (1753). Much-branched annual 10-150 cm, slightly farinose; stem strongly ridged. Lower leaves 3-14 × 1-6 cm, rhombic-hastate with cuneate base, the upper lanceolate to linear, entire. Cymes axillary or in long, spicate inflorescences. Bracteoles 3-7(-20) mm, broadly rhombic, entire or denticulate, smooth or tuberculate dorsally. 2n = 36. {\i Cultivated ground and as a ruderal. Throughout Europe.} All except Sb.
